The paper presents a simulation engine for discrete-event random simulations in C++, which is relevant to multiple sub-categories in computer science. The use of C++ suggests a focus on performance and efficiency, which is relevant to cs.MS (Mathematical Software) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The simulation engine is also based on the resource view, which is relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The simulation of a production system and a database management system suggests a focus on modeling and simulation, which is relevant to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.DB (Databases).
